task.summary: Default task
Added array support to grammar
Fixed a bug in grammar that broke variableDeclaration parsing

Changed ID token to non-greedy syntax, which allowed to move PATH from a lexer token to parser rule, which allowed to handle whitespaces in paths, also changed the way class access works, now there can be path XOR method invocation in one class access, corresponding changes added to ClassAccessVisitor
Added arrays support to classForName
Fixed eol flaw which was resulting in some unexpected parser behavior
Added object instantiation to grammar
Finally found real cause of that eol bug, fixed it

Fixed mess with different type of paths, now path is the same as pathNoDotEnd and classPath (matches "java.lang.String" and not "java.lang." like before), removed outdated commented code from MethodCode
Fixed access modifiers in code
Fixed redundant throw in ObjectField.resolveNames()
Removed unused imports
Applied some final modifiers
Created and implemented ObjectInstantiation class
Finished with implementing object instantiation
Changed method code value rule, to make class access more uniform
Generated antlr4 recognizer and removed all obsolete code
Added some package stuff
Implemented class parsing
Added ClassO code to value visitor
Static field case implementation
Finished ValueVisitor
Changed syntax of variable assignment for future features
Changed Class<?> to ClassO in Variable
Implemented array access
Fixed typo in ArrayAccess and fixed classForName in utils not working correctly on primitive arrays
Implemented array assignement
Implemented array one dimension array instantiation
Implemented multi dimension array instantiation
Added junit5 support to project, will add tests in future
Changed names of get*Name methods in ClassO for better understanding
Documentation for ClassO
More documentation for ClassO
Refactoring, moved ClassO and PackageO to structure package
Added ReflectionMethodContainer class
Replaced reflection Method usages with ReflectionMethodContainer
*Removed getReturnTypeName() and getReturnTypeJvmName() *Replaced .getName() with .getJvmName() in ArrayAccess *Optimized some imports
files: ValueVisitor *Collapsed multiple if blocks to single if-else *Added multiple //region comments to improve readability *Removed multiple occurrences of return null
*Renamed ClassO to ReflectionClassWrapper *Renamed ReflectionMethodContainer to ReflectionMethodWrapper
*Added bytecode equality test
*ReflectionClassWrapper.getMethod() changed in a way to reuse method object instead of creating new one

*Replaced reflection Field usages with ReflectionFieldWrapper *Removed unused hasNonStaticField() and hasStaticField() methods from ClassManagement *Removed unused throws ClassNotFoundException from ObjectField.setNames()
*Code cleanup
*Replaced ArrayList with HashMap in ReflectionCLassWrapper *Fixed code in Variable
*Removed .getTypeString() method from Value interface and all implementations *Moved all PackageManagement logic to PackageO
*Migrated Expression andValue to interface
*Added ClassFactory *Replaced all calls to ReflectionClassWrapper constructor with calls to ClassFactory *Removed unused code from ReflectionClassWrapper
*Added AbstractClassInterface *ReflectionClassWrapper now implements AbstractClass

*Changed Value.getType() return type to AbstractClass *Changed ClassFactory.forName() return type to AbstractClass *Migrated some usages outside of structure package from ReflectionClassWrapper to AbstractClass
*Fixed type conversion in ReflectionClassWrapper.getMethod() *Migrated some usages outside of structure package from ReflectionClassWrapper to AbstractClass
